# KCraft website — GitHub Pages deploy.
#
# The published site is ONLY: the HTML pages, their JS, and loot-data.json
# (fetched by the armoury's Upgrade Finder as a fallback). Everything else
# in this folder — the CSV/DBC build inputs (Spell.csv alone is ~48 MB),
# the spell/itemset build intermediates, the Python build & server scripts,
# backups, logs, secrets — exists only to build the site locally and must
# NOT be pushed.
#
# Strategy: ignore everything, then re-include exactly what the site serves.
# Anything new (another CSV, a .bak, a stray script) is excluded automatically.

# Ignore everything by default.
*

# Re-include only what the live site needs:
!*.html
!*.js
!loot-data.json

# ...and keep this ignore file itself in the repo.
!.gitignore

# If you later add local assets the site loads (CSS, images, fonts, or a
# custom-domain CNAME), re-include them with another ! line, e.g.:
#   !*.css
#   !*.png
#   !CNAME
